Regulation of nephron progenitor cell lifespan and nephron endowment.
In humans, a tenfold variation in nephron endowment between individuals contributes to differences in susceptibility to kidney disease;  however, the mechanisms underlying this variation are not yet clear. Salient advances in our understanding of environmental inputs, and of intrinsic molecular mechanisms that contribute to the regulation of cessation timing or nephron progenitor cell exhaustion, have the potential to inform interventions to enhance nephron endowment and improve lifelong kidney health for susceptible individuals.
